content: As you all know, a bit over a week ago, the Team World Championship ended.
Russia got the first place, Estonia 2nd, China 3rd.
but one game had a value of first place.
In the last round, my game with Sushkov ended with draw.
If I had won it, then Estonia would have been 1st.
And, I was very close to victory.
Maybe I had a sure win, but I missed it.
and see if I could have won the game
and bring Estonia to first place.
For the start, lets have the participation check, and I will put the opening on board meanwhile.
slamduk, Samsone, yuelee00, dongfujia, Yue, tommy, Erica, xuwu, benben, SugarPuffs, Renju_YinLC, derkas, denise, Ikon, Alex, Asuka.
These 26 moves are considered as a standard position,
And even the following move to i4 is very logical.
Normally, black's next move is f5 and then h5.
But I wanted to try something new and challenging,
knowing that Sushkov cannot resist accepting challenges,
so he would definitely follow it.
He spent some minutes of thinking here,
And after 31, he spent nearly an hour.
It was not easy for him to decide.
Playing 32-i5 would lead to standard position,
where black has additional advantage because of unplayed four at f5.
So, after very long thinking, he played k5.
Since black will use fours now,
In my analysis, I had prepared this 39th move,
after which white cannot attack by VCT.
because e4 is too weak point, thanks to black's h4 control.
And the attack by pause moves is impossible, too,
because of black's potential VCF threat at i11.
After long thinking, he chose this 42nd move.
And now, I got a big pressure.
On the 2nd and 3rd table, Tunnet and Ants lost their games.
I knew that draw is not enough
I tried to connect the lower area's power with upper.
But still could not see clear win.
Finally I tried the following plan:
now k2 is double threat point.
I thought, the diagonal of L4_n6 is very strong.
k8, j9 is a threat too
And he played there, of course.
Now I only had 2 minutes on my clock left.
He had more, I think, maybe 10 minutes.
With every move, 30 seconds are added to player's time.
i tried to find win so much.
I thought, maybe like this is good:
but then, i could not find win.
the board is not big enough
then stone 52 makes white very good
and i 12 point can be useful for black later.
but it all didnt matter already
did RT find a sure win afterwards?
It was difficult game for me, because for 2nd day already I had 39C fever.
I could not concentrate very deeply.
One of the best ideas was 43-h13
And this is also the topic of our today's analysis.
Any suggestions for white's next move?
sorry ,i can;t find the best defense
did you see sure black win already?
ok, i take silence as confidence that black cannot win
so, i will challenge one of you now, the silent guys
i will be black, you white
and if you lose, then your silence was laziness, not the real belief that black has nothing
no good move for black now
who can be white here, say me
because white cannot take that spot anyway
This variant has many unanswered questions.
But it looks very interesting, and hopeful for black
And it is interesting that such variant decided the world champion of teams.
Maybe even other 41st moves should be considered.
It is very interesting, and useful variant.
I suggest you all analyse it at home.
Maybe you can find good continuation for black.
yes,i am very interesting in this
